{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|みなもと}}

Derived from {{com|ja|sort=みなもと|水|tr1=mi|t1=[[water]]|pos1=combining form|な|tr2=na|pos2={{inh|ja|ojp|sort=みなもと|-}} possessive particle|[[元]], [[本]]|tr3=moto|t3=[[origin]], [[source]]}}.<ref>{{R:Daijisen}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/>

Vovin believes that the ''na'' in the initial ''mina-'' element is not a genitive particle, but rather actually meant "water", contending that the ''mi'' was instead the honorific prefix {{m|ja|御|tr=mi-}}.<ref>{{cite-book|author=Vovin, Alexander|authorlink=Alexander Vovin|title=Man'yoshu, Book 14: A New English Translation Containing the Original Text, Kana Transliteration, Romanization, Glossing and Commentary|year=2012,|publisher=Brill|page=57}}</ref>

